%e A214618 13^2 + 7^3 = 2^9 = 512. The numbers 13, 7, and 2 form a coprime set and 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/9 < 1. Therefore 512 is a term.
%e A214618 The factorizations of the known terms are 3^2, 3^4, 2^9, 71^2, 122^2, 15613^3, 65^7, 113^7, 21063928^2, 30042907^2. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Dec 22 2013
